    "It forces one to design an explicit plan and the script itself provides an exact record of what was done, making it easier to report in scientific publications. 2.",
    "Once the script is written, it is simple to make a change at any step in the data processing pipeline.",
    "Doing so simply means one has to rerun the script instead of manually performing all the analysis steps again. 3.",
    "A script provides a verifiable procedure that enables testing each individual step, and enables examining the impact on a study's conclusions of changing a parameter or other choice made at any of these steps.",
    "Finally, we get to the terrain of developing one's own tools, the terrain of software engineers."
